    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n`test/functional/channel_spec.lua:123`, ` it('chansend sends lines to terminal channel in proper order'`\n```\ncommand([[let id = jobstart(']] .. sh .. [[', {'term':v:true})]])\n    screen:sleep(50) -- Wait some time for the shell to start.\n    command([[call chansend(id, ['echo \"hello\"', 'echo \"world\"', ''])]])\n    -- With PowerShell the command may be highlighted, so specify attr_ids = {}.\n    screen:expect({ any = [[echo \"hello\".*echo \"world\"]], attr_ids = {} })\n    command('bdelete!')\n    screen:expect({ any = '%[No Name%]' })\n```\nwhen we expect `echo \"hello\"....`, it may go fail at high cpu usage on Windows, probably because it takes longer to setup terminal in Windows, and exceed the time limit `expect` set.\n\nI notice this happen especially in CICD, in functional test of Windows. Of course, pass a larger timeout  param here would always work, but maybe consider scale a timeout factor especially for Win? Or little refactor of `expect` , put `retry` block inside `expect`?\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\ncd build directory of neovim\n$env:TEST_FILE=\"test/functional/terminal/channel_spec.lua\"\n$env:TEST_ARGS=\"--repeat=50 --no-keep-going\"\nstress your cpu like about 90+% usage, i use CPUSTRES from Microsoft SysinternalsSuite\nninja functionaltest\n\n### Expected behavior\n\ntest pass\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.13.0-dev-485+g7673adc952\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWindows 11 25H2\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nPowerShell 7.6.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nN/A\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from src",
